  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improving Cassava Processing Enterprises in Northern Communities Sierra Leone</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Cassava is a staple food crop in Sierra Leone but the Northern Province, struggling to recover from the effects of civil war and the Ebola crisis, local cassava farmers and processors are unable to access the services and support they need to increase the amount they grow and produce reasonably priced cassava products. This project aims to enable cassava farmers and processors to form co-operatives able to access the training, machinery and financial support needed to bring high quality, locally sourced cassava products to market and, as they grow, create local jobs. It aims to reduce hunger and increase the local quality of life.</narrative>
  </description>
